sn.def:
a tall feather palm of northern Brazil (Orbignya barbosiana) with hard-shelled nuts yielding a valuable oil (
               babassu oil
            ) and a kind of vegetable ivory.

entry.def:
any of numerous predaceous aquatic insects of the family Notonectidaesuch as 
            Notonecta undulata
         ) that swim on their backs and may inflict painful bites; -- also called boat bug.

sn.def:
The bully tree (Minusops globosa); also, its milky juice (
               balata gum
            ), which when dried constitutes an elastic gum called chicle, or chicle gum.

sn.q:
And see where surly Winter passes off,
Far to the north, and calls his ruffian blasts;
His blasts obey, and quit the howling hill.

Here is a lady that wants breathing too;
And I have heard, you knights of Tyre
Are excellent in making ladies trip.
